cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.MM

The paper deals with improving the quality of depth channels in RGBD images using probabilistic generative models and natural image statistics. This involves computer vision (cs.CV) techniques for processing RGBD images, graphics (cs.GR) for generating high-quality examples, machine learning (cs.LG) for training generative models, artificial intelligence (cs.AI) for developing the Bayes Least Squares estimator, and multimedia (cs.MM) for dealing with image and video data.
